                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="20593" author="fabio" created="Wed, 1 Nov 2006 21:24:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2790&quot; title=&quot;Wrong  Javadoc description for UrlFilenameViewController.extractViewNameFromUrlPath&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-2790&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-2790&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for a related issue which indirectly explains the origin of the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="20644" author="springboy" created="Sat, 4 Nov 2006 01:44:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Fabio&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have amended the Javadoc for the UrlFilenameViewController to be explicit about the view name determination in Spring 1.2.x and Spring 2.0, and I have added a section to the breaking changes section of the Spring 2.0 reference documentation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is indeed a breaking change; please do accept my apologies for not making this explicit in the documentation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers&lt;br/&gt;
Rick&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="20658" author="fabio" created="Sun, 5 Nov 2006 19:53:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was no big issue to me, and in the end it forced me to refactor some code that is now better than before.&lt;br/&gt;
I hope it may help others to avoid troubles migrating from 1.2.8 to 2.0. I regret a bit I didn&apos;t test 2.0 earlier, I could have spared this little problem to creep into the final distribution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ciao, Fabio.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
